                        <li class="">
                        <div id="s-lg-content-34900002" class="s-lg-book clearfix"><div class="s-lg-book-props"><a href="http://catalogue.library.ryerson.ca/record=b2890341" target="_blank" onclick="return springSpace.springTrack.trackLink({link: this,_st_type_id: '3',_st_content_id: '34900002'});"><span id="s-lg-book-cover-34900002" class="s-lg-book-cover"><img loading="lazy" alt="Cover Art"  src="//syndetics.com/index.aspx?isbn=9781443457590/LC.GIF&client=ryera" class="pull-left s-lg-book-cover-img-0" /></span><span id="s-lg-book-title-34900002" class="s-lg-book-title">Living debt-free : the no-shame, no-blame guide to getting rid of your debt.</span><span id="s-lg-book-by-34900002" class="s-lg-book-by"> by </span><span id="s-lg-book-author-34900002" class="s-lg-book-author">Simmons, Shannon Lee</span></a> <span tabindex="0" class="fa fa-lg fa-info-circle"  data-toggle="popover" data-trigger="hover focus" data-placement="bottom" data-html="true" data-title="Description" data-content="&quot;Whether you have a rolling balance of $3,000 on your credit card or an $80,000 line of credit you are positive you will never pay down, debt can be stressful &ndash; you get locked In a Debt Loop, and it can be easy to lose motivation. You vow to be on your best spending behaviour ever, but then spend money, beat yourself up about it, spend more money and finally give up on your debt repayment plan altogether because it all feels hopeless &ndash; what&rsquo;s another $400 on your credit..." ><span class="sr-only">"Whether you have a rolling balance of $3,000 on your credit card or an $80,000 line of credit you are positive you will never pay down, debt can be stressful – you get locked In a Debt Loop, and it can be easy to lose motivation. You vow to be on your best spending behaviour ever, but then spend money, beat yourself up about it, spend more money and finally give up on your debt repayment plan altogether because it all feels hopeless – what’s another $400 on your credit card if you already owe $4,000? It doesn’t have to be like this. You and your bank account deserve better. After working with thousands of financial planning clients, Shannon Lee Simmons knows that it is possible to have a life and pay down debt at the same time. In fact, that’s the only way your debt repayment plan will work. In Living Debt-Free, you will learn to take control of your spending and pay down your debt in a realistic way that will keep you motivated long enough to see it through to the very last payment. No shame. No blame. No scare tactics. Life is complex. Debt is complex. Living Debt-Free will help you build your realistic plan – the one that will help you finally get rid of your debt, start fresh and feel good about your money again." -- Book jacket.</span></span><div class="s-lg-book-prop-callno">Call Number: HG179.S592L 2018</div><div class="s-lg-book-prop-isbn">ISBN: 9781443457590</div><div class="s-lg-book-prop-pubdate">Publication Date: 2018</div></div></div></li>
